```r
nfl_analytics_theme <- function(..., base_size = 12) {
  
  theme(
    text = element_text(family = "Lexend",
                        size = base_size,
                        color = "black"),
    axis.ticks = element_blank(),
    axis.title = element_text(face = "bold"),
    axis.text = element_text(face = "bold"),
    plot.title.position = "plot",
    plot.title = element_markdown(size = 16,
                                  vjust = .02,
                                  hjust = 0.5),
    plot.subtitle = element_markdown(hjust = 0.5),
    plot.caption = element_markdown(size = 8),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    panel.grid.major =  element_line(color = "#d0d0d0"),
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "#f7f7f7"),
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#f7f7f7"),
    panel.border = element_blank(),
    legend.background = element_rect(color = "#F7F7F7"),
    legend.key = element_rect(color = "#F7F7F7"),
    legend.title = element_text(face = "bold", hjust = .5),
    strip.text = element_text(face = "bold"))
}
```

# Offensive EPA 


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin  -->

```r
(team_offensive_epa <- play_by_play_2024 %>% 
  group_by(posteam) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(posteam)) %>% 
  summarise(avg_offensive_epa = mean(epa, na.rm = TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop') %>% 
  rename(team = posteam))
```

What's the combined record of teams in each quadrant?


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin  -->

```r
df_team_epa %>% 
  ggplot(.,
         aes(x=avg_offensive_epa,
             y=avg_defensive_epa,
             alpha=if_else(team == 'PIT', 'PIT', 'Other'))) + 
  # geom_point(color=df_team_epa$team_color, size=3.5) + 
  geom_image(aes(image = team_logo_wikipedia), size=.1) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0,
             color = "black", linewidth = 0.8, linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0,
             color = "black", linewidth = 0.8, linetype = "dashed") +
  scale_alpha_manual(values = c('PIT' = 1,
                                'Other' = .2)) + 
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(),
                     labels = scales::comma_format()) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(),
                     labels = scales::comma_format()) +
  labs(x='Average Offensive EPA',
       y='Average Defensive EPA',
       caption='Source: nflreadr:: package') + 
  ggtitle('**Average Expected Points Added**: Offense vs. Defense',
          subtitle = '2024 season') + 
  nfl_analytics_theme() + 
  theme(legend.position = 'none')
```

```r
play_by_play_2024 %>% 
  filter(!is.na(posteam)) %>% 
  group_by(posteam) %>% 
  summarise(avg_epa_per_play = mean(epa, na.rm = TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop') %>% 
  left_join(x=.,
            y=teams,
            by=c('posteam' = 'team_abbr')) %>% 
  ggplot(.,
         aes(x = avg_epa_per_play,
             y = reorder(posteam, avg_epa_per_play))) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = if_else(avg_epa_per_play >= 0,
                              "#2c7bb6", "#d7181c")),
           width = 0.2) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, color = "black") +
  scale_fill_identity() +
  geom_image(aes(image = team_logo_wikipedia),
             asp = 16/9, size = .035) +
  labs(x='EPA per Play',
       y='',
       title = "**Offensive Expected Points Added per Play**",
       subtitle = "*2024 Regular Season*",
       caption = "*Inspired by An Introduction to NFL Analytics with R*") + 
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(n = 6)) +
  scale_y_discrete(expand = c(.05, 0)) +
  nfl_analytics_theme() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_blank())
```

```r
play_by_play_2024 %>% 
  filter(!is.na(posteam)) %>% 
  group_by(defteam) %>% 
  summarise(avg_epa_per_play = mean(epa, na.rm = TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop') %>% 
  left_join(x=.,
            y=teams,
            by=c('defteam' = 'team_abbr')) %>% 
  ggplot(.,
         aes(x = avg_epa_per_play,
             y = reorder(defteam, -avg_epa_per_play))) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = if_else(avg_epa_per_play >= 0,
                              "#d7181c", "#2c7bb6")),
           width = 0.2) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, color = "black") +
  scale_fill_identity() +
  geom_image(aes(image = team_logo_wikipedia),
             asp = 16/9, size = .035) +
  labs(x='EPA per Play',
       y='',
       title = "**Defensive Expected Points Added per Play**",
       subtitle = "*2024 Regular Season*",
       caption = "*Inspired by An Introduction to NFL Analytics with R*") + 
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(n = 6)) +
  scale_y_discrete(expand = c(.05, 0)) +
  nfl_analytics_theme() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_blank())
```

```r
(defensive_epa_runpass <- play_by_play_2024 %>% 
  filter(play_type %in% c('run', 'pass')) %>% 
  group_by(defteam, play_type) %>% 
  summarise(avg_epa = mean(epa, na.rm = TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop') %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = play_type, values_from = avg_epa) %>% 
  left_join(x=.,
            y=teams,
            by=c('defteam' = 'team_abbr')) %>% 
    ggplot(.,
         aes(x=run,
             y=pass)) + 
  geom_image(aes(image = team_logo_wikipedia), size=.1) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0,
             color = "black", linewidth = 0.8, linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0,
             color = "black", linewidth = 0.8, linetype = "dashed") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(),
                     labels = scales::comma_format()) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(),
                     labels = scales::comma_format()) +
  labs(x='Against the Run',
       y='Against the Pass',
       caption='Source: nflreadr:: package') + 
  ggtitle('**Average Defensive Expected Points Added**: Run vs. Pass',
          subtitle = '2024 season (through Week 7)') + 
  nfl_analytics_theme() + 
  theme(legend.position = 'none'))
```

```r
passing_epa <- pbp_plus_ftn_2024 %>% 
  filter(!is.na(passer)) %>% 
  group_by(passer, posteam) %>% 
  summarise(plays = n(),
            count_drops = sum(is_drop, na.rm = TRUE),
            interceptions = sum(interception, na.rm = TRUE),
            sum_qb_epa = sum(qb_epa, na.rm = TRUE),
            sum_qb_epa_drops = sum(qb_epa[is_drop == TRUE], na.rm = TRUE),
            sum_qb_epa_int = sum(qb_epa[interception == 1], na.rm = TRUE),
            sum_qb_epa_sack = sum(qb_epa[sack == 1], na.rm = TRUE),
            sum_qb_epa_incomplete = sum(qb_epa[incomplete_pass == 1], na.rm = TRUE),
            sum_qb_epa_dpi = sum(qb_epa[penalty_type == 'Defensive Pass Interference'], na.rm = TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop') %>% 
  filter(plays >= 25) %>% 
  mutate(
    across(
      starts_with("sum"),
      list(
        # mean = ~round(mean(., na.rm = TRUE), 2),
        # zscore = ~scale(.),
        mean_centered = ~. - mean(., na.rm = TRUE)
      ),
      .names = "{.fn}_{.col}"
    )) %>% 
  arrange(-sum_qb_epa_int)
```

```r
play_by_play_2024 %>% 
  filter(!(play_id == 1192 & game_id == '2024_05_LV_DEN')) %>% 
  filter(!is.na(posteam)) %>% 
  group_by(defteam) %>% 
  summarise(avg_epa_per_play = mean(epa, na.rm = TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop') %>% 
  left_join(x=.,
            y=teams,
            by=c('defteam' = 'team_abbr')) %>% 
  ggplot(.,
         aes(x = avg_epa_per_play,
             y = reorder(defteam, -avg_epa_per_play))) +
  geom_col(aes(fill = if_else(avg_epa_per_play >= 0,
                              "#d7181c", "#2c7bb6")),
           width = 0.2) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0, color = "black") +
  scale_fill_identity() +
  geom_image(aes(image = team_logo_wikipedia),
             asp = 16/9, size = .035) +
  labs(x='EPA per Play',
       y='',
       title = "**Defensive Expected Points Added per Play**",
       subtitle = "*2024 Regular Season (through Week 7)<br>Excludes Pat Surtain's pick 6 to see its effect on value*",
       caption = "*Inspired by An Introduction to NFL Analytics with R*") + 
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(n = 6)) +
  scale_y_discrete(expand = c(.05, 0)) +
  nfl_analytics_theme() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_blank())
```

```r
(defensive_epa_runpass_wo_surtain_pick6 <- play_by_play_2024 %>% 
  filter(!(play_id == 1192 & game_id == '2024_05_LV_DEN')) %>% 
  filter(play_type %in% c('run', 'pass')) %>% 
  group_by(defteam, play_type) %>% 
  summarise(avg_epa = mean(epa, na.rm = TRUE),
            .groups = 'drop') %>% 
  pivot_wider(names_from = play_type, values_from = avg_epa) %>% 
  left_join(x=.,
            y=teams,
            by=c('defteam' = 'team_abbr')) %>% 
    ggplot(.,
         aes(x=run,
             y=pass)) +

             color = "black", linewidth = 0.8, linetype = "dashed") +
  geom_vline(xintercept = 0,
             color = "black", linewidth = 0.8, linetype = "dashed") +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(),
                     labels = scales::comma_format()) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = scales::pretty_breaks(),
                     labels = scales::comma_format()) +
  labs(x='Against the Run',
       y='',
       caption='Source: nflreadr:: package') + 
  ggtitle('',
          subtitle = "<span style='color:#FB4F14'>**Excludes Pat Surtain's pick 6**</span>") +
```

```r
player_stats_17_24 <- load_player_stats(seasons = 2017:2024,
                                        stat_type = 'offense')
```

<!-- rnb-text-begin -->

<!-- rnb-source-begin  -->

```r
(int_rate_17_24 <- player_stats_17_24 %>% 
  filter(position == 'QB') %>% 
  group_by(recent_team, player_name, season) %>% 
  summarise(
    across(
      c(attempts, interceptions),
      list(
        sum = ~sum(., na.rm = TRUE)
      ),
      .names = "{.fn}_{.col}"
    ),
    .groups = 'drop') %>% 
  mutate(int_rate = sum_interceptions / sum_attempts) %>% 
  filter(sum_attempts >= 100))
```

```r
int_rate_17_24 %>% 
  filter(player_name == 'P.Mahomes') %>% 
  ggplot(.,
         aes(x=season,
             y=int_rate)) + 
  geom_col() + 
  geom_mean_lines(aes(y0=int_rate)) + 
  geom_text(aes(label = paste(round(int_rate*100, 1), '%', sep='')),
            nudge_y = -.002, color='white', family='Lexend', fontface='bold') + 
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent) + 
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(2017, 2024, 1)) +
  labs(x='',
       y='INT rate') + 
  ggtitle('Pat Mahomes has **doubled** his career average interception rate',
          subtitle = 'INT rate = interceptions / attempts<br>Does not exclude throw aways') + 
  nfl_analytics_theme()
```
